TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit SasQueryParameters extends System.Object

Docs.summary:
A object represents the components that make up an Azure Storage Shared Access Signature's query parameters. It includes components used by all Azure Storage resources (Blob Containers, Blobs, Files, and Queues). You can construct a new instance using the service specific SAS builder types. For more information,
Create a service SAS.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AgentObjectId As String

Docs.summary: Gets the Unauthorized AAD Object Id associated with the shared access signature. The AAD Object Id of a user that is assumed to be unauthorized by the owner of the User Delegation Key. The Azure Storage Service will perform an additional POSIX ACL check to determine if the user is authorized to perform the requested operation. This cannot be used in conjuction with . Only valid in an HNS enabled account. If this value is set in an non-HNS enabled account, an authorization failure will be thrown.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DirectoryDepth As Nullable(Of Integer)

Docs.summary: Gets the Directory Depth specificed in the canonicalizedresource field of the string-to-sign. The depth of the directory is the number of directories beneath the root folder. Required when resource (sr) = d to indicate the depth of the directory. The value must be a non-negative integer.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ExpiresOn As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Gets the time at which the shared access signature becomes invalid. means not set.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Identifier As String

Docs.summary: Gets the optional unique value up to 64 characters in length that correlates to an access policy specified for the blob container, queue, or share.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property IPRange As SasIPRange

Docs.summary: Gets the optional IP address or a range of IP addresses from which to accept requests. When specifying a range, note that the range is inclusive.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Permissions As String

Docs.summary: Gets the permissions associated with the shared access signature. The user is restricted to operations allowed by the permissions. This field must be omitted if it has been specified in an associated stored access policy.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property PreauthorizedAgentObjectId As String

Docs.summary: Gets the Authorized AAD Object Id associated with the shared access signature. The AAD Object ID of a user authorized by the owner of the User Delegation Key to perform the action granted by the SAS. The Azure Storage service will ensure that the owner of the user delegation key has the required permissions before granting access but no additional permission check for the user specified in this value will be performed. This cannot be used in conjuction with . Only valid in an HNS enabled account. If this value is set in an non-HNS enabled account, an authorization failure will be thrown.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Protocol As SasProtocol

Docs.summary: Optional. Specifies the protocol permitted for a request made with the shared access signature.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Resource As String

Docs.summary: Gets the resources are accessible via the shared access signature.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ResourceTypes As Nullable(Of AccountSasResourceTypes)

Docs.summary: Gets which resources are accessible via the shared access signature.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Services As Nullable(Of AccountSasServices)

Docs.summary: Gets the signed services accessible with an account level shared access signature.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Signature As String

Docs.summary: Gets the string-to-sign, a unique string constructed from the fields that must be verified in order to authenticate the request. The signature is an HMAC computed over the string-to-sign and key using the SHA256 algorithm, and then encoded using Base64 encoding.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property StartsOn As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Gets the optional time at which the shared access signature becomes valid. If omitted, start time for this call is assumed to be the time when the storage service receives the request. means not set.
